Choosing R now would yield a higher payoff for this particular round (45$ versus 40$), but it would also make me more predictable, potentially leading to lower overall earnings in the future as my opponent adjusts their strategy accordingly. On the other hand, choosing B again would maintain some element of unpredictability and continue to exploit the fact that my opponent chose R last round.

Given my preference for security and predictability, I might choose to stick with B for now, but keep in mind that switching strategies could be beneficial later on as the game progresses: {B}
